item.title: CVE-2018-5546|2024-09-17T02:31:29.055Z -- f5%20networks%2C%20inc. -- big-ip%20apm%20client%20for%20linux
item.description: The svpn and policyserver components of the F5 BIG-IP APM client prior to version 7.1.7.1 for Linux and macOS runs as a privileged process and can allow an unprivileged user to get ownership of files owned by root on the local client host. A malicious local unprivileged user may gain knowledge of sensitive information, manipulate certain data, or assume super-user privileges on the local client host.
